        <heading>Section </heading>
        <content>
          <p>CHAPTER 5.  OF THE PRICE OF THE CONTRACT OF SALE
Art. 2464.  Price, essential elements
The price must be fixed by the parties in a sum either certain or determinable through a method agreed by them.  There is no sale unless the parties intended that a price be paid.
The price must not be out of all proportion with the value of the thing sold.  Thus, the sale of a plantation for a dollar is not a sale, though it may be a donation in disguise.</p>
        </content>
